      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(ui): reset routed sessions to main on restore",
        "body": "Closes #61661\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes an issue where Control UI users could reload into a stale historical routed session instead of the real `main` session when older persisted routed keys were restored from settings. That left the UI appearing misrouted after reload even though the backend session state was expected to fall back to `main`.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThis change preserves valid scoped `sessionsByGateway` routed selections for the active gateway while sanitizing legacy top-level routed session values back to `main` before restored state is used. The fix also keeps the allowed and disallowed restore paths explicit with focused storage coverage and browser-level Control UI proof, without changing live gateway routing or backend session semantics.\n\n## User Impact\n\nUsers can reopen Control UI without being dropped into an obsolete routed session from old persisted settings. Valid scoped routed selections still restore for the active gateway, while legacy top-level routed values now normalize safely to `main` during reload.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Current head: `2d718489a7da952b7188d3843e13d0e5a0ee5f2e` (`fix(ui): simplify routed restore key parsing`).\n- Current-head focused validation passed:\n  - `CI=true COREPACK_HOME=/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/agents/pr-machine/workspace/.corepack node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.ui.config.ts ui/src/ui/storage.node.test.ts --maxWorkers=1`\n  - `CI=true COREPACK_HOME=/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/agents/pr-machine/workspace/.corepack node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.test.ui.json --incremental false --pretty false`\n  - `CI=true COREPACK_HOME=/home/node/.openclaw/workspace/agents/pr-machine/workspace/.corepack pnpm -s lint`\n  - `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD`\n  - `git merge-tree --write-tree HEAD upstream/main`\n- Real behavior proof carried on the current branch:\n  - Current-head browser-level Control UI E2E coverage is included via `ui/src/ui/e2e/session-restore.e2e.test.ts`, covering both reload paths: legacy top-level routed keys normalize to `main`, while scoped per-gateway routed selections survive reload.\n  - The PR also carries copied terminal proof from `pi-pr-lab` for the focused storage restore path, where `ui/src/ui/storage.node.test.ts` passed with `1` file and `52` tests on the proof checkout used for the routed-session reload scenarios.\n- Current worker revalidation for this body refresh:\n  - authenticated GitHub API read of PR `#78741`, recent PR comments, and the current upstream `.github/pull_request_template.md`\n  - `git fetch upstream --prune`\n  - `git fetch origin --prune`\n  - `git merge-tree --write-tree origin/fix/control-ui-routed-session-restore upstream/main` -> clean tree `173182bf5d14904828ea514bcfb149a9f86181b0`\n- Remaining proof limitation: this worker container cannot launch local Chromium because `libglib-2.0.so.0` is missing, so the browser-level proof for the current branch is represented by the checked-in E2E coverage and the previously recorded current-branch validation already attached to the PR history.\n",
